<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/719.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Haitian Legation in this city has not notified the Department of the
                            death of President Auguste or of the election of his successor,
                            President Oreste. But if the Government of Haiti has officially informed
                            you that President Oreste has been elected in accordance with the
                            Constitution of Haiti you may attend all functions connected with his
                            inauguration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>